Erythrina edulis

   [5805.gif]
   Authority Triana ex M. Micheli
   Family Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Fabales:Leguminosae
   Synonyms Erythrina esculenta
   Common names basul, balù, antipurutu, baluy, chachafruto, chafruto,
   sachafruto, sachapuruto, calù, frisol ca1ù, nopas, pajuro, sachaporoto,
   sacha purutu
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 5805

   Notes
   Latitude:
   Altitude: It is generally grown between 1800-2200 m in the central
   Andes, between 1100-2700 m in Colombia and between 900-3200 in Peru.
   Temperature: Reported temperature range for growth is 5-25°C with the
   optimum between 15-22°C. It does not tolerate frequent frosts.
   Water: Reported annual rainfall range for growth is 450-1800 mm with
   the optimum between 600-1500 mm. It does not tolerate long periods of
   drought, especially during early stages of establishment.
   Radiation
   Range & intensity: It is a pioneer species that grows best in full
   sunlight, but trees can tolerate some shade in the early stages of
   growth.
   Photoperiodism: The trees requirements are unknown, but other members
   of the genus set seed to the limits of the subtropics.
   Soil:
   Physical: The tree grows well in loose-textured sandy loams and in
   heavy clay soils and can grow in a wide range of well drained soil.
   Chemical: It does not grow well in strongly acidic soils. Reported soil
   pH range for growth is 4.5-8 with the optimum between 5.5-7.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
